I have tested this as well as I can, but there still could be some bugs (and
there very probably are!), therefore, to protect myself I must include the
following statement:-

By using this software you agree to take full responsibility for any actions
this software makes, including all possible damage to files, hardware (can
it?) and software.

Also, I built this binary distribution using the GNU C version contained in
the file "mfgcc258.zoo" from Atari.Archive's Mint hierarchy, this is a
version for the Falcon/TT (ie. 68030). I'm hoping that the -m68000
compilation flag used when compiling this package has produced proper 68000
code without any 68020 instructions added, I haven't been able to resurrect
my old 520STM to test it. If the programs contained within this package do
not run and you are using a 68000 based Atari machine please e-mail me
immeadiately at the following address:-

	Stephen.Usher@earth.ox.ac.uk

